                    <msContents n="2">
                        <!--increment n attribute for ms containing multiple ms items-->
                        <summary> This fragmentary palm-leaf manuscript is part of a bundle of a few manuscripts
                            (Or.715), all seemingly composed of collections of Buddhist <term xml:lang="san">stotra</term>s. Five different manuscripts, all
                            from around the 12th-13th century, have been tentatively identified on
                            paleographical and codicological grounds. Further research might shed more light on the
                            subdivision of the whole manuscript bundle. 
                        </summary>
